# How to Make a BLT Sandwich (Best Ever Recipe) If you’re looking for the best ever BLT sandwich recipe, then look no further. This classic sandwich is made with bacon, lettuce, tomato, and mayonnaise on toasted bread. It's the perfect balance of savory and sweet, crispy and soft, and salty and fresh flavors. ## BLT Sandwich Ingredients To make a delicious BLT sandwich at home, you’ll need the following ingredients: - 4 slices of bread (preferably sourdough or thick cut white bread) - 8 slices of crispy cooked bacon - 1 large ripe tomato, sliced - 1 head of lettuce or 8 leaves of romaine lettuce, washed and dried - Salt and pepper to taste - Mayonnaise for spreading Optional additions: avocado, red onion, pickles, or hot sauce. ## BLT Sandwich Instructions To make a BLT sandwich, follow these easy steps: 1. Cook the bacon until crispy: Preheat a large skillet over medium heat and cook 8 slices of bacon until crispy. Remove with a slotted spoon and place on paper towels to drain excess grease. Set aside. 2. Toast the bread: Preheat your broiler or a pan to toast the bread slices. Lightly spread mayonnaise on one side of each slice of bread. Place the slices under the broiler or in the pan and lightly toast until golden brown. 3. Assemble the sandwich: Start by spreading mayonnaise on the toasted side of two slices of bread. Lay down 4 slices of cooked bacon on top of one slice of bread, followed by a generous amount of lettuce leaves. Season the lettuce with salt and pepper. Place the tomato slices on top of the lettuce. Add a few slices of avocado (optional) on top of the tomatoes. Place the other slice of bread on top, mayonnaise side down. 4. Cut and serve: Use a serrated knife to carefully cut the sandwich in half. Serve immediately and enjoy! ## Tips for Making the Best BLT Sandwich Here are some helpful tips to ensure your BLT sandwich turns out amazing every time: - Use crispy cooked bacon: Make sure the bacon is cooked until it's nice and crispy, as this will add texture and flavor to the sandwich. - Toast the bread: Toasting the bread lightly adds a nice crunch and enhances the flavors of the sandwich. - Use ripe tomatoes: A ripe, juicy tomato is essential for a great BLT sandwich. Make sure to use one that's in season and has a slight give when gently squeezed. - Don’t skimp on the lettuce: The lettuce adds texture, freshness, and helps balance out the saltiness of the bacon. Use plenty of it! - Optional additions: Feel free to add other ingredients like avocado, red onion, pickles, or hot sauce for extra flavor and texture.